main event: A round, white object resembling the 'flame-out' of an aircraft was observed by military personnel on radar and visually for about 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was initially sighted at an elevation of 45 degrees and an azimuth of 333 degrees (12:50 o'clock position), and then moved to an overhead position at 298 degrees.
The object disappeared when the aircraft turned, suggesting it may have been some type of artificial satellite or satellite-like object.
The report suggests the object was moving at a high altitude and was observed for a relatively short duration.
The weather conditions were clear with unrestricted visibility, and the object was observed during the night.
The report was filed by a 2nd Lieutenant Intelligence Officer, who determined the object was likely an orbiting satellite or some type of artificial space vehicle.
result: Probable satellite or artificial space vehicle
